results.definition: lying beyond what is openly revealed or avowed (especially being kept in the background or deliberately concealed)
examples: looked too closely for an ulterior purpose in all knowledge"- Bertrand Russell

results.definition: beyond or outside an area of immediate interest; remote
examples: a suggestion ulterior to the present discussion
without...any purpose, immediate or ulterior"- G.B.Shaw

results.definition: coming at a subsequent time or stage
